                       FilterCollection filter,
                       float pre,

        Initialize the variables for this set of templates
        Parameters:
        stat - Station collection has all of the information about the station

        pre - The pre-event memory to fetch in seconds
        tlen - The length of the templates in samples

      • getTemplates

        public void getTemplates(java.lang.String outputpath,
                         java.lang.String eqphasedata,
                         boolean ref,
                         float maxdistance,
                         java.lang.String cwbip,
                         int cwbport,
                         boolean outputwaveforms,
                         float shift)
                  throws java.io.IOException
        Used by SubspacePreprocess Get waveform templates from Query. This is done at start-up or when a new event is located and potentially added to the detection
        Parameters:
        outputpath - output directory
        eqphasedata - A phase line from the configuratin
        ref - Is this the reference event?
        maxdistance - Skip any where this distance from the reference location is found
        cwbip - Where to get the data
        cwbport - and its port
        outputwaveforms - If true, write out SAC files with the data
        shift - The amount to shift this waveform in seconds ( that is start the waveform this much before usual start)
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - if one occurs

      • filterData

        public static void filterData(float[] data,
                              float hp,
                              float lp,
                              int npoles,
                              int sps,
                              java.lang.String filtertype)
        Filter the given data with a new filter constructed from the other arguments
        Parameters:
        data - Array of data to filter
        hp - high pass corner
        lp - Low pass corner
        npoles - Number of poles
        sps - Data rate in hertz
        filtertype - filter type "lowpass", "highpass", "bandpass"
